cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with navigation of robots in human crowds. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the approach involves inferring the velocity and goal of agents based on their spatial orientation. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the approach involves training a local interaction model using real human trajectory data. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the approach involves predicting future trajectories of agents based on their past behavior. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still relevant as the paper deals with modeling human-human and human-robot interactions in crowded settings.
